The Indian navy searched for aborigines on the Nicobar islands to prevent their extinction after the tsunami.
The Jawara tribe occupies 639 sq km on Andaman islands, while the Sentinelese are reclusive.
Five tribes, totaling 989 people, survived the tsunami.
Coral reefs in the Indian Ocean are recovering slowly.
Mangroves play a crucial role in protecting coastlines.
The tsunami severely damaged marine life, especially coral reefs.
Mangroves shielded some areas from the tsunami's impact.
Efforts are underway to rehabilitate damaged mangroves for coastal protection.
The tsunami's impact on marine life is expected to be long
